Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.68,0:00:08.36,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Abandoned artificial satellites.\NTanks jettisoned from shuttles.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.01,0:00:11.65,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Refuse generated during\nspace station construction.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.25,0:00:19.30,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This vast amount of junk floating in space,\nspace debris, is a very serious threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.30,0:00:27.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is a story of 2076, a time in which\nthis space garbage has become a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.43,0:00:29.97,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hull separation mechanism\nsystem check.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.64,0:00:33.40,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Couplers, power transmission,\nguidance and control.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.04,0:00:35.66,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Connection of all systems\nto avionics confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.71,0:00:40.12,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Moving elements of gravity\nadjustment mechanism...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.12,0:00:44.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Awesome! This baby's fresh\noff the assembly line!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.49,0:00:46.71,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's still in the wrapper!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.45,0:00:49.61,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Fee! Can I rip\nthis off?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.62,0:00:50.54,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Knock yourself out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.54,0:00:53.83,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah! I love this stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.21,0:00:59.00,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like a\ncaptain already!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.40,0:01:02.88,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's like a kid who\njust got a new toy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.85,0:01:05.10,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Men are kids their\nwhole lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.14,0:01:08.86,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, check this out!\NIt's got a D5 instead of a D2!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.08,0:01:12.48,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tanabe, you have\na visitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.60,0:01:14.90,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What, here?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.26,0:01:18.27,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She said that she's been waiting for you to\nreturn to Seven, so I brought her on board.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.27,0:01:19.07,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.07,0:01:20.10,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Me, that's who!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.37,0:01:21.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Lucie?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.36,0:01:23.51,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have something important to talk\nto you about. Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.72,0:01:25.34,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Someplace where\nwe can be alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.75,0:03:02.38,F.O. (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\move(520,370,310,355)\fad(760,830)\bord0.1\shad2\fs20\fscx150\fscy100\t(0,5500,\fscx210\fscy160)}Turning Point
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.30,0:03:05.70,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You like him,\ndon't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.60,0:03:09.13,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.43,0:03:09.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Have you slept\nwith him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.11,0:03:11.75,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.94,0:03:13.68,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't done anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.31,0:03:16.37,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we did\nalmost kiss, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.50,0:03:17.95,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.15,0:03:21.90,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,At first, I thought he was just\nsome irresponsible guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.80,0:03:27.16,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But when he chews me out over something,\nit's really because he has pride in his job.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.51,0:03:31.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And he has a\nsoft side, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.85,0:03:34.78,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When I'm practicing, he stays with me\nuntil I can do it properly on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.49,0:03:38.61,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And he's got a strong sense of justice,\nand he likes kids a lot, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.50,0:03:41.96,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Uh... What are you\ntalking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.96,0:03:42.17,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,remember, -senpai is an honorific when used with a name, thus you need to add it here. not your mistake, just a technicality you probably didnt know :)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.17,0:03:45.40,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What I'm saying is, we almost kissed.\NHachimaki-senpai and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.35,0:03:47.76,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,With Diaper Man?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.09,0:03:53.14,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, stop calling him that!\NAll astronauts wear diapers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.22,0:03:58.64,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm dense about these things,\nso I never realized how I felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.54,0:04:01.59,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You noticed it first,\ndidn't you, Lucie?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.39,0:04:06.73,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder when I started feeling\nthis way about him? I always...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.91,0:04:09.33,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm sorry. I'm doing all the talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.47,0:04:11.75,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You wanted to talk about\nsomething, right, Lucie?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.32,0:04:13.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.82,0:04:16.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.30,0:04:18.78,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Um, with what?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.79,0:04:19.49,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.34,0:04:22.12,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there, Tanabe!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.54,0:04:30.05,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to this! Toy Box 2 can\nmake it to the moon on its own, and can even land\non the surface!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.47,0:04:32.33,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The engine's a\nlaser-ignition model,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.34,0:04:35.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and if we added extra tanks, it might\neven be able to go all the way to Mars!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.02,0:04:36.80,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Hachi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.72,0:04:39.47,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How's Tanabe-san been lately?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.62,0:04:44.36,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She's been giving me the cold shoulder ever\nsince the Space Defense Front incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.16,0:04:47.90,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I asked her out to dinner a while ago,\nbut she turned me down.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.63,0:04:49.48,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Has she said anything\nto you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.74,0:04:50.94,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.06,0:04:54.54,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.57,0:04:56.73,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, crap! I totally\nforgot about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.29,0:05:13.35,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We went that far, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.82,0:05:16.83,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So I have to do\nthis right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.35,0:05:18.33,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As the man...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.53,0:05:21.49,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've gotta do it right...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.50,0:05:28.16,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai, we're supposed to mix this in\nwith the ferret feed, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.19,0:05:29.96,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,See it through all the way. To the bitter end.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.40,0:05:31.08,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.90,0:05:34.48,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. I'm sorry, I wasn't listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.73,0:05:36.37,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have Earth-lag?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.38,0:05:41.77,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Your mom's pork cutlets were\N delicious, and the sea was pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.15,0:05:44.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's not surprising that\nyou miss the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.33,0:05:45.88,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tanabe...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.22,0:05:46.52,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.02,0:05:50.15,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Um... Once we're off, do you want\nto go grab something to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.37,0:05:52.84,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, we can go once Fee-san and Yuri get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.84,0:05:53.52,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's not\nwhat I meant!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.41,0:06:01.63,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I... I meant\njust you and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.05,0:06:03.89,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You don't want to?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.71,0:06:09.76,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've been meaning to\ntell you something...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.77,0:06:13.11,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Listen up, everyone! The following\nis an order from the manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.98,0:06:15.32,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Orders from\nthe manager?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.58,0:06:16.95,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Orders from the\nassistant manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.30,0:06:19.62,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Um, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.04,0:06:25.06,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Effective today, I am hereby banning office\ndating here in Second Division, Debris Section!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.25,0:06:29.40,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Did you say something?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.95,0:06:34.40,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's less than 100 days until the\NVon Braun's\noutfitting is to be completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.83,0:06:38.28,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, the shipping schedule for\nthe tandem mirror engine hasn't been fixed yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.81,0:06:41.32,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like the load was\ntoo much for Claire.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.86,0:06:43.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Following through on the matter\nwas your job as her superior.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.10,0:06:45.81,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like nothing better than\nto offer her some guidance,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.14,0:06:48.16,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...but she seems to be rather\nbusy with other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.12,0:06:50.54,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She's over at the OSA\nright now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.06,0:06:54.77,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I see it was a mistake to let her oversee the\NOrbital Security Operating Audit, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.59,0:06:58.49,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Her mistakes have been\nawfully conspicuous lately, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.33,0:07:01.37,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps you should assign\Nsomeone else to oversee it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.76,0:07:06.94,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We'll accept it this time, but be more\ncareful from now on, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.96,0:07:08.42,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I will. I'm terribly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.60,0:07:10.68,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When can we expect\nthe attached forms?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.20,0:07:12.10,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sometime next week.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.32,0:07:15.71,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Make it before the end of this week.\NI'm going on vacation next week.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.87,0:07:20.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do that. You need Form 35, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.59,0:07:21.55,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yep, that's the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.71,0:07:33.26,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.16,0:07:35.77,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.50,0:07:40.78,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Could you please tell me?\NHow is Temara Poitier doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.08,0:07:44.47,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tanabe-kun, you know about Third Division, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.68,0:07:46.04,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They're our\nlunar division, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.04,0:07:50.35,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Right. The daughter of their division manager\nworks for Technora as a receptionist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.51,0:07:52.31,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She got pregnant recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.33,0:07:53.91,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that wonderful news?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.91,0:07:54.78,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's not!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.13,0:07:56.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What, they don't know\nwho the father is?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.12,0:08:00.09,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, he's a scientist who also\nworks for Third Division.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.32,0:08:01.83,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, an office romance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.30,0:08:04.16,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They say the division manager\nis raging mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.37,0:08:06.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All of Third Division is\nin turmoil right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.93,0:08:08.09,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.10,0:08:09.96,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's the manager's daughter and\na rank-and-file employee!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.19,0:08:11.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Their social standings\nare too different!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.23,0:08:12.51,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What do social standings\nhave to do with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.70,0:08:14.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Inside a company,\nit matters plenty.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.36,0:08:16.36,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, what's happened\nto the two kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.36,0:08:19.64,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The boy's been reassigned\nto a mining plant on Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.80,0:08:21.47,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They can't do that! It's not right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.72,0:08:23.59,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They can't break up two people\nwho love each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.87,0:08:26.29,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There's no such thing as labor or\N management where love is concerned!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.29,0:08:28.47,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look, in a company,\nthere are!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.71,0:08:31.38,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it, that Kuroda boy who\ntransferred here recently asked to come here...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.61,0:08:37.06,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...because he couldn't stand working in the\nsame department as his ex-girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.09,0:08:41.49,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,See what I mean?\NOffice romances\ncause all sorts of trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.68,0:08:42.72,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Still, that doesn't\nmean you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.93,0:08:45.22,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it makes you feel sorry\nfor them, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.44,0:08:48.44,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Chief, it wasn't just the regular\nemployee who was demoted.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.64,0:08:49.26,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They didn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.27,0:08:51.93,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They did! They shipped his\nsupervisor off to Mars, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.94,0:08:53.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He was on the verge of retirement,\nbut that didn't stop them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.17,0:08:59.04,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Officially, it's for an expansion of\nour Mars environmental business.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.90,0:09:02.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe something like that happened\nwhile we were on vacation...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.69,0:09:06.66,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, office romances are\nbanned for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.73,0:09:08.73,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.74,0:09:10.01,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.15,0:09:11.83,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's an order from the\nsection chief, Tanabe-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.07,0:09:13.53,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,From the assistant\nsection chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.83,0:09:16.88,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please understand, Ai-chan.\NI'm going to be retiring soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.27,0:09:18.30,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please! Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.30,0:09:19.53,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hachi! That goes\nfor you, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.74,0:09:20.70,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you\ntelling me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.93,0:09:22.04,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You have a history of it,\nremember?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.76,0:09:25.82,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You used to go out with that Claire girl\nover in Control Section, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.00,0:09:27.05,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,H-How did you\nknow that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.27,0:09:28.87,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ai-chan mentioned it\na while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.81,0:09:32.73,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Claire-san dumped you because\nyou say mean things like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.72,0:09:35.90,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ha-chan, is there anyone\nthat you're interested in?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.13,0:09:38.74,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't seeing someone\nalready, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.19,0:09:42.82,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, there isn't! I'm not seeing anybody,\nand I'm not interested in anybody!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.07,0:09:47.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Technora women might be real go-getters,\nbut they've all got ugly personalities!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.81,0:09:54.04,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's that, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.43,0:09:55.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.04,0:09:56.57,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, thanks for your\nunderstanding, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.58,0:10:00.74,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I still haven't...\nagreed to anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.14,0:10:09.49,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's a tall order... And it's a big rush, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.93,0:10:12.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You've got that test flight\nto the moon tomorrow, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.83,0:10:15.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All right, I'll try to get everything\ntogether before then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.89,0:10:17.35,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about that. I owe you one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.27,0:10:20.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. I'll see you at 1900 hours, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.80,0:10:21.28,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.82,0:10:24.28,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri, did something happen\ndown on Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.25,0:10:25.55,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You think I've changed?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.03,0:10:29.95,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A future engineer broke\nsomething for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.53,0:10:33.24,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The part of me that couldn't\nlet go of the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.33,0:10:49.55,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Temara Poitier is being held under\nextremely humane conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.10,0:10:54.29,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,However, I'm told that all the research data\nfor his spacesuit was confiscated.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.62,0:10:57.20,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Because the technology could be applied\ntowards weapons, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.68,0:10:59.20,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you standing\nup for him?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.73,0:11:03.06,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is it sympathy? Or out of\nopposition to INTO?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.00,0:11:04.76,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.94,0:11:08.79,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose I'll never be\none of the nobility...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.17,0:11:12.57,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What are you\nmad about?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.95,0:11:13.99,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not mad!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.26,0:11:16.15,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you are! I said that because...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.08,0:11:18.59,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Because of the ban\non office romances.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.02,0:11:22.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's what you get\nfor blabbing!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.46,0:11:25.69,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's better this way, isn't it? Now you don't\nhave to make do with what's on hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.71,0:11:27.15,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, don't be\nso sarcastic!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.17,0:11:28.72,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't help it, I have\nan ugly personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.72,0:11:31.75,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look, that was me\nresponding in kind!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.97,0:11:32.54,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.97,0:11:33.60,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's prohibited!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.51,0:11:36.68,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Going any farther\nis now prohibited.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.23,0:11:44.83,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Cheng-Shin-san!\NWhat's that you're reading?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.35,0:11:48.14,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The documentation on the Von Braun.\NIt's going to Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.80,0:11:50.99,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They're going to start taking\ncrew applications soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.20,0:11:52.07,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're joining\nthe crew?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.34,0:11:53.90,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I plan to take\nthe test.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.90,0:11:57.75,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is Jupiter we're talking about!\NYou won't come back for seven years!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.75,0:11:58.58,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose not...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.38,0:12:00.58,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How can you\nsay it like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.32,0:12:08.14,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Calling Seven,\nthis is DS-12.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.60,0:12:11.75,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We are go for taking free. Main umbilical, separate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.53,0:12:14.29,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Separation complete. You copy?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.58,0:12:16.31,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I copy. Taking free.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.47,0:12:28.85,Alternative (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs24\pos(355,443)}DS-12, this is Seven. Establishing datalink via Navstar.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.29,0:12:26.50,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen\nbetween those two?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.75,0:12:27.39,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What two?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.60,0:12:28.86,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hachi and Tanabe-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.15,0:12:30.09,Alternative (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(355,443)}Datalink confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.15,0:12:30.84,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs25}Things seem to be awfully chilly between those two.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.34,0:12:32.99,Alternative (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We will be making orbital plane change\nusing ME to reach transfer orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.86,0:12:32.05,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(355,473)}It's just one of their usual fights.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.51,0:12:33.54,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(355,473)}It's nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.79,0:12:34.48,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.81,0:12:35.64,Alternative (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...so we will separate using OMS\nuntil we reach changeover point.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.29,0:12:37.35,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It seems a little different\nfrom their usual ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.09,0:12:39.04,Alternative (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please verify vector\nand window datalink.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.91,0:12:46.35,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,DS-12, this is Seven. Vector and window\nnavigation data matrix downlink complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.27,0:13:11.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are we there yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.62,0:13:15.11,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We're at Lagrange One, running\na translink test with the Fishbones.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.39,0:13:18.93,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really? I guess I'll go\nback to sleep, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.18,0:13:24.80,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Tanabe...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.60,0:13:29.78,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,About Apollo Park... I said I'd take you there,\nremember? Once we reach the moon, we...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.80,0:13:33.47,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No thanks. Why don't you go by yourself\nand try to score with some girls, Senpai?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.84,0:13:36.28,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You never let things go,\ndo you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.53,0:13:38.56,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Better that than forgetting\neverything like you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.56,0:13:39.55,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Forget what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.56,0:13:41.56,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You don't remember what you tried\nto do to me on Earth, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.56,0:13:43.07,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,M-Moron! Don't bring up that crap here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.47,0:13:45.44,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"That crap"? What do you mean, "That crap"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.69,0:13:47.26,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, just forget\nabout it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.37,0:13:53.25,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Abort the translink test.\NA meteoroid\nis coming at us along our trajectory.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.61,0:13:55.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I copy. C'mon, Tanabe,\nwe're heading back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.74,0:13:59.12,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I know that! I can hear Fee-san's\N transmissions over here, too, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.45,0:14:02.33,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I was just getting confirmation, damn it!\NDon't bite my head off!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.66,0:14:04.39,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't help it. I have an ugly personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.66,0:14:03.34,Alternative (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.21,0:14:07.11,Alternative (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,DS-12! DS-12, please respond!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.95,0:14:06.29,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Would you give it a rest?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.50,0:14:10.71,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,DS-12, do you read? Come in, DS-12.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.11,0:14:13.34,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is DS-12. We read you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.52,0:14:14.43,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.43,0:14:17.64,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness we got through!\NWho's in charge over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.64,0:14:23.07,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Technora's Second Division, Debris Section\N(Assistant) Manager, Arvind Lavie.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.10,0:14:24.60,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the highest ranking\nperson aboard this ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.74,0:14:28.59,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please, Mr. Manager.\NYou've got to save our dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.49,0:14:32.70,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Our experiment module is along\nthe meteoroid's path.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.23,0:14:35.76,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It'll only be two more days before\nour experiments produce results.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.37,0:14:42.89,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We beg of you. Is there anything\nyou can do to save our module?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.16,0:14:44.12,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.31,0:14:46.13,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's one of our company's\nunmanned modules.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.36,0:14:48.55,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir. I'm sorry, I forgot to introduce myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.99,0:14:53.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Ning Mantegna. I'm a scientist with\NTechnora's Third Division, Research Section.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.58,0:14:57.03,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mantegna? Oh, pregnancy boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.14,0:14:57.89,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Pregnancy boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.89,0:15:00.74,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You know, the guy who knocked up\nthe daughter of Third Division's manager!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.44,0:15:05.45,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it. You said you'd\ndo the right thing, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.63,0:15:08.60,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah! It's that stupid old man's fault\nfor not giving you two his blessing!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.79,0:15:09.22,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.22,0:15:09.84,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.02,0:15:10.47,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.46,0:15:14.27,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.04,0:15:18.54,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We've spent five years researching\ncatch connective tissue...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.92,0:15:21.94,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...to create a new concept\nin armor material.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.60,0:15:24.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But we're going to be split up\nand transferred next week.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.57,0:15:27.19,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is our\nlast chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.39,0:15:29.65,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm fully aware of your\ncircumstances, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.77,0:15:32.59,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That guy is one\nnarrow-minded dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.71,0:15:35.89,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please help! You're the only ones\nanywhere near here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.85,0:15:39.68,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let our last dream die. Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.05,0:15:42.69,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.06,0:15:44.27,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it, Hachimaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.27,0:15:47.06,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We might be able to do something for them\nif we use our impact drivers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.22,0:15:49.70,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I mean!\NDestroying meteoroids is prohibited!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.88,0:15:50.98,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're prohibiting\nthis, too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.07,0:15:53.56,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You only have a license to\ncollect debris, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.86,0:15:56.19,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Meteoroids are natural bodies,\nnot debris!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.19,0:15:57.78,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's that got to do\nwith anything?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.78,0:16:01.24,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Everything! There's a little thing called\nthe Space Environmental Protection Act!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.24,0:16:03.22,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you break INTO law,\nyou'll be a criminal!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.36,0:16:07.45,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm your superior, so I'll be held responsible!\NI won't be able to support my children!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.45,0:16:10.69,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Which means that if I move the module,\nthere's no problem, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.81,0:16:13.81,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Um. Well, I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.96,0:16:15.84,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Would that work?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.84,0:16:16.78,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.01,0:16:19.31,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Second Division.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.53,0:16:21.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't sweat it. I'm doing this 'cause I want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.54,0:16:26.22,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You should also do what you want.\NForget about parents or your company rank.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.73,0:16:34.71,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.19,0:16:37.98,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A little over three minutes\nto collision, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.50,0:16:40.78,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If I use my return fuel, too,\NI should be able to...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.88,0:16:43.09,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's far enough, men\nof the Second Division.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.30,0:16:43.89,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What the...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.82,0:16:47.85,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We of the Third Division are\nin charge of Lunar orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.04,0:16:50.81,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have to ask Second Division\nto stay out of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.11,0:16:52.25,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell\nare you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.49,0:16:55.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Norman Schwimmer,\NDivision manager\nof Third Division.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.46,0:16:57.20,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Division Manager, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.42,0:16:58.57,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The dumb daddy, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.01,0:17:02.26,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Manager, please! Let us\ncomplete this experiment!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.45,0:17:04.30,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What do you hope to accomplish\nby researching sea cucumbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.57,0:17:09.01,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be better for the company to let that meteoroid\N hit the module and collect the insurance money.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.21,0:17:12.20,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So you knew that the meteoroid was coming, and you still...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.81,0:17:13.28,Alternative (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Cut off their\ntransmission.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.73,0:17:16.72,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please, sir! What happened to your daughter\nis my responsibility, no one else's!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.78,0:17:23.32,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have to ask you to walk away\nfrom this, Second Division.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.41,0:17:24.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir! At once, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.81,0:17:29.51,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hachi, come back here! That's an order\nfrom the Third Division manager!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.69,0:17:32.42,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Second Division.\NHe's got no no authority over us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.46,0:17:35.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But you're still a mere rank-and-file employee.\NAre you going to disobey a superior?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.92,0:17:39.63,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Damn right I am. This doesn't have anything\nto do with who's labor and who's management
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.63,0:17:41.84,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Collision in two minutes, 25 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.00,0:17:42.62,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You little fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.04,0:17:45.68,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In my jurisdiction, rank-and-file employees\naren't allowed to backtalk their superiors!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.68,0:17:46.32,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Shove it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.11,0:17:49.56,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When somebody tells me something's\nprohibited or tells me to stop something,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.97,0:17:52.39,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...that makes we wanna\ndo it even more!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.02,0:17:55.48,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you talk to me\nthat way, you little peon!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.27,0:18:03.49,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, crap. It's got too much mass.\NOne Fishbone doesn't have the thrust to...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.95,0:18:04.43,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.32,0:18:06.28,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll help!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.78,0:18:10.15,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, don't rush it. Stay calm and link up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.49,0:18:11.05,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I copy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.41,0:18:14.12,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Avionics control\nmaster-to-slave couplers, in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.11,0:18:17.08,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Connection complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.64,0:18:20.52,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, we'll do a de-orbit burn with our\ncombined thrusters. Punch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.75,0:18:21.39,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I copy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.42,0:18:24.15,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Balancing remaining propellant.\NAdjusting common center of gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.34,0:18:28.55,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Darn those two... All right, we'll just have\nto cut off the module's location data feed...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.34,0:18:26.25,Alternative (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Composite vector now along axis of thrust.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.55,0:18:30.34,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No one but the captain is\N allowed to touch the controls.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.52,0:18:33.01,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Yuri-kun, what do you\nthink you're doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.54,0:18:34.09,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hachimaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.36,0:18:37.05,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sending you the vector for the rendezvous\ncoordinates, so push 'em over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.22,0:18:37.79,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.38,0:18:41.90,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This sector belongs to Third Division!\NI'm the top dog around here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.35,0:18:43.65,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you listening to me?! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.65,0:18:44.57,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Shove it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.07,0:18:47.12,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't do something here,\nit's gonna create debris!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.56,0:18:49.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you expect us to sit back\nand do nothing?! Do you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.08,0:18:52.29,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, start pushing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.54,0:18:53.73,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.11,0:18:57.28,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Combustion at maximum. Continuing to\nincrease thrust and build up delta-V!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.97,0:19:00.05,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Will cut thrust once\ntransfer orbit reached!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.67,0:19:02.36,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Secondary hull,\nseparate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.83,0:19:05.66,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Linkage joints, disengaged.\NLaser guidance control, confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.17,0:19:07.24,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Separation complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.59,0:19:08.22,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Target acquired.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.56,0:19:11.85,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Guidance control. Fine-tuning relative velocity\nwhile in neutral position to target.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.26,0:19:14.48,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Rendezvous complete. Vectors synchronized!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.92,0:19:15.48,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Catch up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.15,0:19:23.14,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Target secured. Ignition!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.10,0:19:28.09,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Experiment module EM42\nis exiting its orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.59,0:19:30.05,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Target meteoroid\nwill make a near miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.47,0:19:35.06,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Put me through to Second Division.\NI want to talk to their boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.80,0:19:39.85,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.44,0:19:45.53,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do we have\na connection?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.13,0:19:47.73,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Barely. It's voice-only.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.30,0:19:48.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.62,0:19:51.01,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's the man\nfrom earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.32,0:19:54.83,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Section Division crew,\ndo you read me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.06,0:19:56.65,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we read you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.04,0:20:00.35,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you. Now we can go\nto Mars with no regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.85,0:20:01.66,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.23,0:20:04.42,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We've decided to continue\nour work on Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.67,0:20:06.09,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I hope your experiments\nare successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.49,0:20:08.89,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and give my best\nto your girlfriend, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.91,0:20:12.85,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You could always take her with you\nto Mars, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.38,0:20:16.32,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I copy!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.16,0:20:19.85,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much, Debris Section.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.45,0:20:21.33,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Over and out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.71,0:20:26.77,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The division manager's gonna have my hide...\NWhat'll it be? Dismissal, demotion, a pay cut?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.80,0:20:27.69,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't be\nso sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.88,0:20:34.24,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If there's one thing that Dolf's always hated,\nit's being ordered by someone to do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.17,0:20:38.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, are you listening to me? Your people\nacted improperly inside my jurisdiction!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.44,0:20:42.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How do you intend to\nmake amends for this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.28,0:20:43.14,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You have\nmy apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.74,0:20:46.14,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,However, they did what they did to\N prevent the creation of debris, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.80,0:20:48.70,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They did what the Debris Section\nis supposed to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.72,0:20:51.89,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?!\N They screwed things up inside my turf!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.89,0:20:54.72,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you'd like to lodge a complaint,\ncould you do it in an official document?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.34,0:20:58.08,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure to include concrete examples of\nhow they breached company regulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.04,0:21:10.74,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,These new ships sure run through\nthe breathing sequence fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.03,0:21:14.48,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think we'll be okay?\NWe disobeyed a division manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.51,0:21:17.77,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When somebody tells me something's prohibited\N or orders me to stop, it makes we want to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.15,0:21:20.91,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I bet Lavie-san is passed out\nin the cockpit.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.67,0:21:25.04,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said, if somebody says\nsomething is prohibited, l...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.05,0:21:27.86,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Right, right. You already said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.20,0:21:29.94,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tanabe...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.16,0:21:30.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.78,0:21:34.91,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Office romances are\nprohibited, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.35,0:21:40.58,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tanabe, um... About you and me...\NDo you want to...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.34,0:21:43.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.23,0:21:47.22,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wha...?! What're you saying,\nyou pervert?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.54,0:21:50.17,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs24}How could I possibly say yes if you ask me like that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.20,0:21:51.81,Alternative (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,M-Moron, I didn't\nmean that!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.03,0:21:56.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I meant... picking up where\nwe left off on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.18,0:21:59.28,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm asking you if you want\nto go out with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.85,0:22:00.69,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do I have to spell it out?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.44,0:22:01.47,Alternative (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How am I supposed to know that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.92,0:22:04.19,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,For one thing, you've\ngot no delicacy!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.59,0:22:07.63,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You go through other people's drawers\nand you walk around in your diapers!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.65,0:22:09.39,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look who's talking! You wear diapers, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.99,0:22:14.73,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'm saying that\nyou've got no delicacy!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.85,0:22:25.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, what's it gonna be?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.96,0:22:28.66,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Your answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.05,0:24:58.86,F.O. (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\shad0.5\bord0.2}{\fscx115\1c&HD2BEAC&}{\move(242,15,435,15)}{\fad(0,500)}Next Time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.05,0:24:58.86,F.O. (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs20\shad0.5\bord0.2\fscx140\fscy140\1c&HD2BEAC&\move(478,366,263,363)\fad(0,500)}In her Case...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.15,0:24:40.30,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The deal will be made here at Seven.\NThis trio came up here yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.64,0:24:45.56,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Would you mind if I took\nthe afternoon off?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.43,0:24:53.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I came here\nto see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.54,0:24:57.48,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Say something,\ndamn it.
